<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="19" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" type="basionym">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Basionym.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Steud" authorityYear="1854" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Urachne" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fusca">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Urachne fusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Nees ex Steud., Syn. Pl. Glumac. 1(2): 123. 1854 [1855 publ. 2-3 Mar 1854]. Lectotypus: K000433539, Herbarium Hookerianum 1867 (http://specimens.kew.org/herbarium/K000433539), imaginem videmus; Isolectotypi K000433540, Herbarium Benthianum 1854 (http://specimens.kew.org/herbarium/K000433540), imaginem videmus; CGE, Herb. J. Lindley, purchased 1866 (figs 1, 2, 3); &quot;prope Valparaiso, Chili; H. Cuming 453, 1831; Imagines videmus.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/10606" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" start="Figure 1" startId="F1">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Figure 1.</emphasis>
Isotype of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkworth, Ciald., &amp; Gandhi" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Barkworth, Ciald., &amp; Gandhi" baseAuthorityYear="2014" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Piptochaetium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fuscum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Piptochaetium fuscum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
deposited at CGE, the Cambridge University Herbarium, England. Image used with permission.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="19">
<pageBreakToken pageId="2" pageNumber="19" start="start">The</pageBreakToken>
three specimens are from the same gathering and conform to the protologue. We chose K000433539 as the lectotype because it has more material, both reproductive and vegetative, than the other specimens. 
<bibRefCitation author="Columbus, JT" journalOrPublisher="Aliso" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" pagination="65 - 767" refId="B7" refString="Columbus, JT, Smith, JP, 2010. Nomenclatural changes for some grasses in California and the Muhlenbergia clade (Poaceae). Aliso 28: 65 - 767" title="Nomenclatural changes for some grasses in California and the Muhlenbergia clade (Poaceae)." volume="28" year="2010">Columbus and Smith (2010)</bibRefCitation>
were forced to base their name on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Phil" authorityYear="1858" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Piptochaetium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="purpuratum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Piptochaetium purpuratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Phil. because the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. E. Hubb" authorityYear="1925" class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Poaceae" genus="Stipa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Graminales" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="fusca">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Stipa fusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had already been used for an Australian taxon by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hubbard, CE" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Miscellaneous Information" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" pagination=": 432" refId="B9" refString="Hubbard, CE, 1925. Decades Kewenses, Plantarum novarum in herbario horti regii conservatorum Decas CXIII. Bulletin of Miscellaneous Information 1925: 432" title="Decades Kewenses, Plantarum novarum in herbario horti regii conservatorum Decas CXIII." volume="1925" year="1925">Hubbard (1925)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="19">
<bibRefCitation author="Parodi, LR" journalOrPublisher="Aliso" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" refId="B11" refString="Parodi, LR, 1944. Revision de las gramineas Australes Americanas del genero Piptochaetium. Revista del Museo de la Plata, Bot.6: 1-310." title="Revision de las gramineas Australes Americanas del genero Piptochaetium. Revista del Museo de la Plata, Bot. 6: 1 - 310." year="1944">Parodi (1944)</bibRefCitation>
stated that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkworth, Ciald., &amp; Gandhi" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Barkworth, Ciald., &amp; Gandhi" baseAuthorityYear="2014" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Piptochaetium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fuscum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Piptochaetium fuscum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grew in central Chile, extending from Valparaiso and Santiago to Valdivia. This statement was confirmed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Zuloaga, FO" journalOrPublisher="Catalogo de las plantas vasculares del Cono Sur." pageId="4" pageNumber="21" refId="B19" refString="Zuloaga, FO, Morrone, O, Belgrano, MJ, 2008. . Catalogo de las plantas vasculares del Cono Sur. Vol. 1" volume="Vol. 1" year="2008">Zuloaga et al. (2008)</bibRefCitation>
who added that it grew at 0-800 m. There are only three South American records with latitude and longitude in the Global Biodiversity Information Facility. They were collected at 
<geoCoordinate degrees="37.41" direction="south" orientation="latitude" precision="555" value="-37.41">37.41S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="72.01" direction="west" orientation="longitude" precision="555" value="-72.01">72.01W</geoCoordinate>
[SI 268952]; 
<geoCoordinate degrees="36.48" direction="south" orientation="latitude" precision="555" value="-36.48">36.48S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="72.71" direction="west" orientation="longitude" precision="555" value="-72.71">72.71W</geoCoordinate>
[BAA 416344], and 
<geoCoordinate degrees="36.56" direction="south" orientation="latitude" precision="555" value="-36.56">36.56S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="72.49" direction="west" orientation="longitude" precision="555" value="-72.49">72.49W</geoCoordinate>
[BAA 416345]. 
<bibRefCitation author="Zuloaga, FO" journalOrPublisher="Catalogo de las plantas vasculares del Cono Sur." pageId="4" pageNumber="21" refId="B19" refString="Zuloaga, FO, Morrone, O, Belgrano, MJ, 2008. . Catalogo de las plantas vasculares del Cono Sur. Vol. 1" volume="Vol. 1" year="2008">Zuloaga et al. (2008)</bibRefCitation>
provide information in terms of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Chileâ€™s">Chile's</normalizedToken>
regions (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Native distribution of Piptochaetium fuscum. Information and base map from Zuloaga et al. (2008), used with permission of Missouri Botanical Garden Press." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/10607" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). The species is also known from one locality in Marin County, California, where it was first collected in 1978 (
<bibRefCitation author="Barber, JC" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" publicationUrl="http://ucjeps.berkeley.edu/consortium/" refId="B3" refString="Consortium of California Herbaria. 2014-01-09. Records of Piptochaetium setosum. http://ucjeps.berkeley.edu/consortium/" title="Consortium of California Herbaria. 2014 - 01 - 09. Records of Piptochaetium setosum." url="http://ucjeps.berkeley.edu/consortium/" year="2009">Consortium of California Herbaria 2014</bibRefCitation>
). The origin of the population is unknown. It does not appear to have spread since its introduction.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/10607" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" start="Figure 2" startId="F2">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Figure 2.</emphasis>
Native distribution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkworth, Ciald., &amp; Gandhi" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Barkworth, Ciald., &amp; Gandhi" baseAuthorityYear="2014" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Piptochaetium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fuscum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Piptochaetium fuscum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Information and base map from 
<bibRefCitation author="Zuloaga, FO" journalOrPublisher="Catalogo de las plantas vasculares del Cono Sur." pageId="4" pageNumber="21" refId="B19" refString="Zuloaga, FO, Morrone, O, Belgrano, MJ, 2008. . Catalogo de las plantas vasculares del Cono Sur. Vol. 1" volume="Vol. 1" year="2008">Zuloaga et al. (2008)</bibRefCitation>
, used with permission of Missouri Botanical Garden Press.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="19">
To determine the conservation status of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkworth, Ciald., &amp; Gandhi" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Barkworth, Ciald., &amp; Gandhi" baseAuthorityYear="2014" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Piptochaetium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fuscum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Piptochaetium fuscum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a search should be made for specimens in Chilean herbaria and field work conducted to locate natural populations. Such activities were beyond the scope of our study.
</paragraph>
